  "prompt": "How is the movie \"Happy New Year\"?",
  "response": "\"Happy New Year\" is a Bollywood film released in 2014, directed by Farah Khan and produced by Gauri Khan under the Red Chillies Entertainment banner. The film features a star-studded cast, including Shah Rukh Khan, Deepika Padukone, Abhishek Bachchan, Boman Irani, Sonu Sood, and Vivaan Shah. It falls into the genre of musical heist comedy-drama.\n\nThe storyline revolves around a team of amateur dancers who enter a dance competition as part of a larger plan to pull off a heist. The film combines elements of comedy, drama, music, and action, typical of Bollywood masala films.\n\n\"Happy New Year\" received mixed reviews from critics. It was praised for its ensemble cast's performances, particularly Shah Rukh Khan and Deepika Padukone, and for its production values, music, and choreography. However, some critics pointed out its over-the-top plot and lengthy runtime as drawbacks.\n\nDespite the mixed critical reception, \"Happy New Year\" was a commercial success, becoming one of the highest-grossing Bollywood films of 2014. If you enjoy light-hearted, entertaining Bollywood films with a blend of comedy, music, and action, \"Happy New Year\" might be worth watching.",
